<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1220,1319]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1256,1282]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Distribution.</emphasis>
This is the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[647,795,1256,1282]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1171,1256,1282]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
(as “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1336,1256,1283]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Rhodesia</collectingCountry>
”) (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, K. G. V. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="488 - 510" refId="ref40306" refString="Smith, K. G. V. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R. (1980) 38. Family Syrphidae. In: Crosskey R. W. (Ed.), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afro- tropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 488 - 510." type="book chapter" year="1980">Smith &amp; Vockeroth 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Whittington, A. E." box="[371,575,1292,1319]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="579 - 607" refId="ref41868" refString="Whittington, A. E. (2003) The Afrotropical Syrphidae fauna: an assessment. Studia dipterologica, 10 (2), 579 - 607." type="journal article" year="2003">Whittington 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,502,1400,1427]" box="[151,502,1400,1427]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,502,1400,1427]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[238,502,1400,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Chrysotoxum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,401,1400,1427]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysotoxum</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1472,1679]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[275,424,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Chrysotoxum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,424,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysotoxum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises large, wasp-mimicking species (
<bibRefCitation author="van Veen, M. P." box="[915,1089,1473,1499]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref41487" refString="van Veen, M. P. (2004) Hoverflies of Northwest Europe. KNNV Publishing, Utrecht, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004274495" type="book" year="2004">
van 
<collectingRegion box="[964,1020,1473,1499]" country="Austria" name="Wien" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Veen</collectingRegion>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
). Species of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Chrysotoxum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysotoxum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are widely distributed in all zoogeographical regions except Australasian and the Antarctic with approximately 150 species mostly in the Palaearctic region (
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. &amp; Pont, A. C. &amp; Thompson, F. C." box="[749,987,1544,1571]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref35348" refString="Evenhuis, N. L., Pape, T., Pont, A. C. &amp; Thompson, F. C. (2008) Biosystematic Database of World Diptera, Version 10. 5. Available from: http: // www. sel. barc. usda. gov / diptera / biosys. htm (accessed 25 February 2013)" type="url" year="2008">
Evenhuis 
<emphasis box="[863,913,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Thompson, F. C. &amp; Rotheray, G. E. &amp; Zumbado, M. A." box="[999,1253,1544,1571]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref41174" refString="Thompson, F. C., Rotheray, G. E. &amp; Zumbado, M. A. (2010) Syrphidae (Flower flies). In: Brown, B. V., Borkent, A., Cumming, J. M., Wood, D. M., Woodley, N. E. &amp; Zumbado, M. A. (Eds.), Manual of Central American Diptera. Vol. 2. NRC Research Press, Ottawa, pp. 763 - 792." type="book" year="2010">
Thompson 
<emphasis box="[1127,1178,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The adult flies of European 
<taxonomicName box="[295,444,1580,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Chrysotoxum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[295,444,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysotoxum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species can be found in deciduous and coniferous forests and grasslands (
<bibRefCitation author="Speight, M. C. D." box="[1270,1425,1580,1607]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref40366" refString="Speight, M. C. D. (2020) Species accounts of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 2020. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera). Vol. 104. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin, 313 pp." type="book" year="2020">Speight 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Larvae are specialized in preying upon root aphids associated with ant nests (
<bibRefCitation author="Rotheray, G. E. &amp; Gilbert, F." box="[1006,1288,1616,1643]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref39858" refString="Rotheray, G. E. &amp; Gilbert, F. (2011) The Natural History of Hoverflies. The Blissett Group, London, xiv + 334 pp." type="book" year="2011">Rotheray &amp; Gilbert 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nedeljkovic, Z. &amp; Acanski, J. &amp; Vujic, A. &amp; Obreht, D. &amp; Dan, M. &amp; Stahls, G &amp; Radenkovic, S." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="84 - 102" refId="ref38303" refString="Nedeljkovic, Z., Acanski, J., Vujic, A., Obreht, D., Dan, M., Stahls, G &amp; Radenkovic, S. (2013) Taxonomy of Chrysotoxum festivum Linnaeus, 1758 (Diptera: Syrphidae) - an integrative approach. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169, 84 - 102. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12052" type="journal article" year="2013">
Nedeljkovic 
<emphasis box="[151,200,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Speight, M. C. D." box="[285,439,1652,1679]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref40366" refString="Speight, M. C. D. (2020) Species accounts of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 2020. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera). Vol. 104. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin, 313 pp." type="book" year="2020">Speight 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
